    deck:
      "Autonomous coding agents that plan, write, test, and ship code with minimal human oversight. The category has split into distinct lanes: platform-integrated (Copilot), open-source (OpenHands), enterprise-managed (Factory), and standalone SaaS (Devin). The key decision is platform-integrated vs standalone, and open-source vs managed.",
    verdict: [
      "GitHub Copilot Coding Agent is the lowest-friction entry point — GA with Jira integration, built-in security scanning, $10-39/mo via existing Copilot tiers. Best for teams already on GitHub.",
      "OpenHands is the open-source standard — 69K+ stars, $18.8M Series A, enterprise logos (AMD, Apple, Google, Netflix, NVIDIA), MIT licensed, self-hostable, model-agnostic.",
